title: Pilot
description: Havenhurst gets a new dean of students, while the freshmen adjust to their first week at college.

title: They Shoot Baskets, Don't They
description: Antonio is advised by the athletic director to take easier classes so he can focus on basketball. While Stroke is unsettled by a psychological test.

title: Breaking up Is Hard to Overdue
description: Patty meets a political upperclassman, while Jessica is charmed by a fellow student and David is invited to a frat party.

title: Midterm Madness
description: Midterms bring about a three-day study session for Stroke and Patty; a moral dilemma for Jessica and David; and an alcohol problem for Whitney.

title: Look Homeward Angela
description: David and Whitney play host to their visiting girlfriends. Meanwhile, Robin is juggling two men at the same time.

title: The Adventures of Pat's Man and Robin
description: Patty is jazzed when she captures the interest of a musician, who also strikes a chord with Robin. Meanwhile, Antonio and Whitney fear they killed an endangered animal.

title: David Is Authorized
description: David develops a relationship with a famous author, who's interested in more than just his writing.

title: The Accused
description: David's favorite professor is accused of racial and gender bias in his choice of textbooks, causing a campus wide debate of multicultural curriculum's. Meanwhile Stroke receives mixed messages from his woman-studies partner.

title: When Whitney Met Linda
description: Whitney starts a relationship with a local girl, but their social differences get in the way. Meanwhile Jessica frets when the dorm bathrooms become co-ed.

title: Parents Weekend
description: It's Parents' Weekend during which David meets Jessica's father, Robin confronts her folks, and Patty gets a surprise from her mother.

title: The Best Little Frat House at Havenhurst
description: Jessica confronts her own ethnicity when an anti-Semitic Flyer is circulated on campus. Meanwhile, David ponders joining a fraternity which is exclusive.

title: Bright Smoke, Cold Fire
description: Jessica and David ponder rekindling their romance; Patty gets fired up about a student film, but must contend with a temperamental director (LeBlanc); and Antonio burns over a gossip column.

title: Greenwich Mean Time
description: Robin considers posing nude for a men's magazine to pay for her tuition, despite outrage from Patty and Jessica. Meanwhile Antonio finds that he's not the boyfriend Janet's father would like for his daughter.

title: Educating David
description: When David's tutoring job pairs him with an Olympic bound female fencer (Bowen), Jessica hopes he doesn't need lessons in devotion.

title: Howie Farr Is Too Far
description: Whitney and Antonio wage a war of practical jokes against Stroke and David, but it's no laughing matter when Robin starts dating a professor.

title: The Jessica File
description: Stroke listens to his heart and starts a relationship with a woman who is hearing-impaired. Meanwhile Whitney and Antonio host a radio show.

title: See You in September
description: The freshmen prepare to leave for their summer destinations, including Ohio for Patty if an audition with a famous actress goes well.
